png2vtf
=======

A small utility that converts an RGBA PNG file into a pseudo-VTF
(Valve Texture Format) file using `IMAGE_FORMAT_A8`.

Note: this is **not** a general-purpose full-color PNG-to-VTF
converter. Only the alpha channel of the input PNG is preserved; the
RGB channels are discarded. The input must be an RGBA PNG
(`PNG_COLOR_TYPE_RGBA`).


Dependencies
============

A C compiler, `make`, `pkg-config`, and `libpng` are required.

Arch Linux:

    sudo pacman -S base-devel libpng pkgconf

Debian / Ubuntu:

    sudo apt install build-essential libpng-dev pkg-config

Fedora:

    sudo dnf install gcc make libpng-devel pkgconf-pkg-config


Build
=====

    make

This uses `pkg-config` to discover the compiler and linker flags for
`libpng`, so no manual configuration is required on a normal Linux
system.


Usage
=====

    ./png2vtf input.png output.vtf


Clean
=====

    make clean
